%% ============================================================
%% Assignment 2 – Agent Turn Automaton
%% ============================================================
%% Models which actions can be taken when within a single turn.
%% One turn = one player's turn (human or agent).
%% Maps to the TurnPhase enum in the Java implementation.
%%
%% ACTION SPACE (what can be taken when):
%%   AWAIT_ROLL     : ROLL only (human types "Roll"; agent auto-rolls)
%%   ROLL_DICE      : (transition) evaluate dice result
%%   ROBBER_DISCARD : (automatic) each player with >7 cards discards half
%%   ROBBER_PLACE   : (automatic) robber placed on random tile
%%   ROBBER_STEAL   : (automatic) qualifying player gives card to roller
%%   POST_ROLL      : (automatic) distribute resources; then -> BUILD_OR_TRADE
%%   BUILD_OR_TRADE : BUILD (settlement | city | road), LIST; repeat or GO
%%   AWAIT_GO       : GO only (blocks until "go" for step-forward R2.4)
%% ============================================================

stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> AWAIT_ROLL : turn starts

    AWAIT_ROLL --> ROLL_DICE : ROLL (human) or auto (agent)

    ROLL_DICE --> POST_ROLL : dice ≠ 7
    ROLL_DICE --> ROBBER_DISCARD : dice = 7

    ROBBER_DISCARD --> ROBBER_PLACE : players with >7 cards discard half
    note right of ROBBER_DISCARD : Round down (R2.5)

    ROBBER_PLACE --> ROBBER_STEAL : robber placed on random tile
    note right of ROBBER_PLACE : Must differ from current tile (R2.5)

    ROBBER_STEAL --> POST_ROLL : qualifying player gives random card to roller
    note right of ROBBER_STEAL : Qualifying = building adjacent to robber tile

    POST_ROLL --> BUILD_OR_TRADE : resources distributed (robber blocks tile)

    BUILD_OR_TRADE --> BUILD_OR_TRADE : BUILD settlement / city / road
    BUILD_OR_TRADE --> AWAIT_GO : GO (done building)

    AWAIT_GO --> [*] : next player's turn (R2.4 step-forward)
    note right of AWAIT_GO : Blocks until "go" command received
